DIGEST
SB 203 Original 2026 Regular Session Lambert
Present law allows possession of three times the daily take limit of largemouth bass, spotted
bass, red drum, and spotted sea trout taken south of US-90 by the licensed fisherman who
took them, where the fisherman can show a public launch receipt showing he has been on
the water or at a remote camp for at least two days. Further requires the fish be kept whole
or gutted, in plastic bags or containers, separated by species and marked with the date taken,
species, number of fish, and name and license number of the fisherman who took them.
Proposed law retains present law and removes the requirement that the caught fish be kept
in plastic bags or containers marked with catch information.
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Amends R.S. 56:325(B)(4) and 325.1(A)(4))
